article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 102, East Central 68
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Jordan Glynn scored 20 points and grabbed 13 rebounds for a double-double as Stephen F. Austin routed East Central 102-68. Jereal Scott had 13 points for the Lumberjacks (7-3), and Eddie Williams added 11. Mark Gomillia and Austin Falke came off the bench to add 10 points each. Eric Allen had 15 points to lead East Central (5-6), and Maurice Abraham had 13 points and nine rebounds. Stephen F. Austin outrebounded the Falcons 50-37 and played well inside, outscoring East Central 60-36 in the paint. The Jacks hit 40 of 71 from the field (56.4 percent), while the Falcons hit 29 of 76 (38.2 percent). Stephen F. Austin was similarly dominant from the foul line, from where the Lumberjacks hit 17 of 24 while only giving East Central 10 attempts. The Falcons made just four free throws.
